rvice/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_diamond_ver01/data/sn87065469/00383344013/1921011301/0038.pdf", "segment_count": 6, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/sn87065469/1921-01-13/ed-1/", "word_coordinates": "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service"}], "segment_id": "/service/ndnp/msar/batch_msar_diamond_ver01/data/sn87065469/00383344013/1921011301/0038.xml", "segments": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn87065469/1921-01-13/ed-1/?sp=1"], "batch": ["msar_diamond_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "composite_location": ["0/united states/", "1/united states/mississippi/", "2/united states/mississippi/lafayette/", "3/united states/mississippi/lafayette/oxford/"], "contributor": ["mississippi department of archives and history"], "date": "1921-01-13", "dates": ["1921-01-13"], "description": ["a EAGLE GEORGE W PRICE Editor and Publish _ WHICH WE FIGHT Subscription 200 per Year In Advance Single Copy 5c Vol 45 Oxford Lafayette County Miss Thursday January 13 1921 No 10 Says Great Navy Only Alternative For Disarmament Daniels Tells Congressmen Proposal to Make IJ S Sea Power Less Than Strongest is Unworthy Washington Jan 11 An in ternational agreement with all or practically all the nations which will guarantee an entl of competition in navybuilding was presented as the only alternative to the building by the United States of a navy power ful enough to command the respects and fear of the world by Secretary Daniels in testimony today before the house naval affairs committee The naval secretary who appeared before the committee in connection with its consideration of the subject of disarmament dismissed as un worthy of discussion a third pro posal for an American navy less than equal to the most powerful sea power in the world because it is a waste of money to spend money on an agency of war which would be helpless if needed in presenting his views to the committee Mr Daniels took occasion to outline the advice which he"], "digitized": tru